==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Energetical
<hw>En`er*get"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to work, be
active, fr. <?/ active. See <er>Energy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having energy or energies; possessing a capacity for vigorous
action or for exerting force; active.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A Being eternally
<xex>energetic</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exhibiting energy; operating with force, vigor, and
effect; forcible; powerful; efficacious; <as>as, <ex>energetic</ex>
measures; <ex>energetic</ex> laws.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Forcible; powerful; efficacious; potent;
vigorous; effective; strenuous.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>En`er*get"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>En`er*get"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Energetics</ent>⟦br⟧
